 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Notebook 24: LangGraph - Real-World Use Cases\n",
    "\n",
    "**🎯 Goal:** To build a complete, end-to-end agent that solves a real-world problem using the concepts we've learned. We will build an **Automated Research Agent**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧩 Use Case: Auto Research Agent\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective:** Given a topic, create an agent that can:\n",
    "1.  **Research:** Search the web for relevant information.\n",
    "2.  **Write:** Compile the gathered information into a coherent report.\n",
    "3.  **Cite:** Add citations or sources to the report.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will use a multi-agent approach with a supervisor to manage the workflow between a **Researcher**, a **Writer**, and an **Editor**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Agent Roles & State\n",
    "\n",
    "- **State:** The state will hold the topic, research findings, the draft report, and the final, cited report.\n",
    "- **Researcher:** This agent will take the topic and use a (mock) search tool to find information.\n",
    "- **Writer:** This agent will take the research findings and write a draft report.\n",
    "- **Editor:** This agent will take the draft, add (mock) citations, and produce the final report."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from typing import TypedDict, Annotated\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\n",
    "from langchain_core.tools import tool\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the state for our research agent\n",
    "class ResearchState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    topic: str\n",
    "    research_data: Annotated[list, operator.add]\n",
    "    draft_report: str\n",
    "    final_report: str\n",
    "    next_agent: str\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define a mock search tool\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def web_search(topic: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Simulates searching the web for a topic.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return f\"Finding 1 for '{topic}': LangGraph is powerful. Finding 2: Multi-agent systems are complex.\"\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define the agent nodes\n",
    "def researcher_node(state: ResearchState) -> dict:\n",
    "    print(\"--- Agent: Researcher ---\")\n",
    "    research_findings = web_search.invoke(state['topic'])\n",
    "    return {\"research_data\": [research_findings], \"next_agent\": \"writer\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "def writer_node(state: ResearchState) -> dict:\n",
    "    print(\"--- Agent: Writer ---\")\n",
    "    report = f\"Report on {state['topic']}:\\n\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(state['research_data'])\n",
    "    return {\"draft_report\": report, \"next_agent\": \"editor\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "def editor_node(state: ResearchState) -> dict:\n",
    "    print(\"--- Agent: Editor ---\")\n",
    "    cited_report = state['draft_report'] + \"\\n\\nSources: [Mock Web Search]\"\n",
    "    return {\"final_report\": cited_report, \"next_agent\": \"end\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "# The supervisor routes to the correct agent\n",
    "def supervisor_router(state: ResearchState) -> str:\n",
    "    return state.get(\"next_agent\", \"researcher\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Assembling and Running the Graph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "workflow = StateGraph(ResearchState)\n",
    "\n",
    "workflow.add_node(\"researcher\", researcher_node)\n",
    "workflow.add_node(\"writer\", writer_node)\n",
    "workflow.add_node(\"editor\", editor_node)\n",
    "\n",
    "workflow.set_entry_point(\"researcher\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# This is a simplified routing. A more robust way is a conditional entrypoint.\n",
    "workflow.add_edge(\"researcher\", \"writer\")\n",
    "workflow.add_edge(\"writer\", \"editor\")\n",
    "workflow.add_edge(\"editor\", END)\n",
    "\n",
    "app = workflow.compile()\n",
    "\n",
    "initial_state = {\n",
    "    \"topic\": \"The Future of AI Agents\",\n",
    "    \"research_data\": [],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "final_state = app.invoke(initial_state)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n--- Final Report ---\")\n",
    "print(final_state['final_report'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💡 Pro Tip: Improving the Agent\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a simple example. To make it more robust, you could:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Add Loops:** Allow the editor to send the report back to the writer for revisions.\n",
    "- **Use Real Tools:** Integrate with a real search API like Tavily or SerpAPI.\n",
    "- **Use More Powerful LLMs:** Use LLMs within each node to generate more sophisticated research questions, drafts, and edits.\n",
    "- **Add Human-in-the-Loop:** Require human approval before publishing the final report."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🏁 Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "You've successfully built a complete, multi-agent system that automates a research task. This same pattern can be applied to a wide variety of use cases:\n",
    "\n",
- **Code Generation & Review:** A developer agent writes code, a tester agent runs it, and a reviewer agent provides feedback.\n",
    "- **Customer Support:** A triage agent routes a user query to a billing agent or a technical support agent.\n",
    "- **Personal Assistant:** An email-reading agent summarizes a request, a calendar agent schedules a meeting, and a notification agent informs you.\n",
    "\n",
    "In the final notebook, we'll cover best practices for building production-ready agents."
   ]
  }
 ],
